'ML STRING' IS A TOOL FOR ADDINGLINES  OF CODE TO YOUR APPLESOFTPROGRAM THAT  WILL POKE A MACHINELANGUAGE PROGRAM IN MEMORY...WITHOUTUSING ANY DATA         STATEMENTS.TO USE IT; ENTER THE NAME OF AMACHINE  LANGUAGE PROGRAM AT THEPROMPT.  THE    PROGRAM MAY NOT BEMORE THAN 230 BYTES.THEN ENTER AN APPLESOFT LINE NUMBERWHERE THE CODE TO LOAD THE MACHINELANGUAGE PROGRAM WILL BE STORED.  IFYOUENTER A LINE NUMBER n; THEN LINES n;n+5; AND n+10 WILL BE USED.AT THIS POINT; A TEXT FILE WILL BEWRITTEN TO THE DISK.  EXEC THIS TEXTFILE TO ADD THE NEW LINES OF CODE TOYOUR CURRENT APPLESOFT PROGRAM.THE TEXT FILE MAY BE DELETED AFTERUSING.